            <fr:anchor>374</fr:anchor>
            <fr:addr type="user">SP-000F</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>SP-000F.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Reflection Principle">Reflection Principle</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Theorem</fr:taxon>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
              <fr:month>5</fr:month>
              <fr:day>29</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:authors />
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[ (B_{t} )_{t\geq  0} ]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link type="local" href="SP-0001.xml" addr="SP-0001" title="Brownian motion">Brownian Motion</fr:link>. Then, for any <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[ t\geq  0 ]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[ a\geq  0 ]]></fr:tex>, it holds that
  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[     \mathbb {P} \left ( \sup _{s\leq  t} B_{s} \geq  a \right )      = 2\mathbb {P} \left ( B_{t} \geq  a \right )      = \mathbb {P} \left ( \left \vert  B_{t}  \right \vert  \geq  a \right )    ]]></fr:tex></fr:p>
            <fr:p>In particular, <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[ \sup  _{s\leq  t} B_{s}  ]]></fr:tex> has the same distribution as <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[ \left \vert  B_{t}  \right \vert   ]]></fr:tex></fr:p>
            <fr:p>A consequence of the reflection principle is that
  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[     \mathbb {E} \left [ {\left ( \sup  _{s\leq  t} \left \vert  B_{s}  \right \vert   \right )}^n  \right ] < +\infty  \quad  \forall  n \in  \mathbb {N}    ]]></fr:tex></fr:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
          <fr:backmatter />
        </fr:tree>
